  "prompt": "What's the most embarrassing thing you've ever said in another language by accident?",
  "response": "I don't have personal experiences, but many people have found themselves in embarrassing situations when speaking another language by accident. For example, English speakers learning Spanish might intend to say \"I'm embarrassed,\" but accidentally say \"Estoy embarazada,\" which actually means \"I'm pregnant.\" This mix-up can lead to some humorous and awkward moments!\n\nAnother common mistake is in French, where someone might try to compliment a friend by saying \"Je suis intelligent\" (\"I am intelligent\") instead of \"Tu es intelligent\" (\"You are intelligent\"). Using the wrong subject can change the meaning and lead to confusion.\n\nThese kinds of errors are a natural part of the language learning process and often become funny stories to share later on!",
